  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening role of STI policies in SDG planning and monitoring in Latin America and the Caribbean</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To strengthen LAC member States capacity to develop, consolidate and monitor inclusive STI and knowledge systems, in particular by providing them with STI information for decision making, and systematizing STI policy instruments, systems, organizational and national STI programs, legislative frameworks in science, technology and innovation indicators date. All these different lines of work will be presented at CILAC 2018 in Panama. CILAC has become UNESCO&apos;s framework for action in STI the region, a space where it can present its flagship initiatives to its partners, exchange with stakeholders from the region and move the science, technology and technology agenda of the region forward.</narrative>
  </description>
